text.tspan: Theophylline-controlled target editing in mammalian cell lines. (a) Vector maps of lentiviral constructs expressing SpyCas9 and various constitutive and
theophylline-inducible sgRNAs. (b) Theophylline titration and target editing in a HEK293-based reporter cell line with doxycycline-controlled GFP expression.
Theophylline concentrations of 5mM and 10mM caused severe cell death (dashed bars). sgGFP9 targets the GFP of the reporter cell line. sgRen71 is a negative
control sgRNA. Note, pCF441-sgGFP9 resulted in a slight decrease of GPF-positive cells, though this trend already started in absence of theophylline. (c) Efficien-
cy and leakiness assessment of sgRNA induction and target editing in a BNL CL.2-based reporter cell line with constitutive GFP expression. Note, theophylline
(1mM) treatment decreased the editing activity of the wild-type Cas9-sgRNA complex (pCF204-sgGFP9). sgGFP9 targets the GFP of the reporter cell line.
